720.question: How much is proposed model better than baselines in performed experiments?
720.response: {'Answer': 'The proposed model GDP performs much better than other baselines for BLEU score and the time spent in training. It outperforms the other two baselines by 0.004 and 0.012 for BLEU score and by 5.95 seconds and 14.27 seconds for the total training time, respectively. It also has a better performance in terms of time spent in the dialogue policy part. However, it is also the largest model in size.'}
720.answer:
most of the models have similar performance on BPRA: DSTC2 (+0.0015), Maluuba (+0.0729)
GDP achieves the best performance in APRA: DSTC2 (+0.2893), Maluuba (+0.2896)
GDP significantly outperforms the baselines on BLEU: DSTC2 (+0.0791), Maluuba (+0.0492)
